This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text summarization. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a model-based approach for verifying factual consistency. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves extracting relevant information from source documents and summaries. Finally, it may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it evaluates the performance of state-of-the-art models for text summarization.
